      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The form of DOUGS FLAME (4) may have appeared to have tapered off but he has been taking on stronger opposition than this. Had been racing consistently earlier this campaign and is well up to winning this with his A-game. LAYDEN (5) is a newcomer from Victoria to the Jarrod Alchin yard and brings some decent form inclining a 3.4m fourth three back at Melton. Has had a month off but Hart drives. Could measure up. IDEAL MARQUESS (3) draws well and is working his way back into form, placing from this barrier two back at Penrith and coming from wider for fifth at his most recent appearance here. CASH AND BLING (10) draws wide but has been quite consistent of late and backs up off a respectable third here on Tuesday.",
